==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Titi
<hw>Ti"ti</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Orig. uncert.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A tree of the southern United States (<spn>Cliftonia
monophylla</spn>) having glossy leaves and racemes of fragrant white
flowers succeeded by one-seeded drupes; -- called also <altname>black
titi</altname>, <altname>buckwheat tree</altname>, and
<altname>ironwood</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any related tree of the genus <gen>Cyrilla</gen>,
often disting. as <altname>white titi</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Titillate</ent>⟦br⟧
